RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 66. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 7 A llowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M YOUR CAPTAIN broke on top and was hustled early from outside, moved clear and angled in after a quarter mile then widened command under urging in the lane. BRIANS WAY broke well then was settled back for two furlongs, progressed two wide on the bend, battled for second inside TRUIST in the stretch and shook off the latter the final sixteenth. TRUIST was away slowly, advanced from outside to threaten three wide on the turn, fought for second in the lane then began to wear down the last sixteenth. SENOR MIKE pressed the early pace, gained the rail into the bend, began to yield, angled to the outside upper stretch and continued to fade. RA'DOM was prominent from inside, checked into the turn, angled out on the bend and had little to offer for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Ra'dom
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, checked into turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Senor Mike
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, angled outside upper stretch, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Brians Way
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 2 wide bid turn, took 2nd near 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: I'm Your Captain
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled early, saved ground, urged stretch until final 70 yards

ENTRY.NAME: Truist
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, 3 wide turn, dueled for 2nd, weakened late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 22000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAYHOP moved to the inside early on, angled out leaving the quarter pole, rallied four wide the last furlong, gradually lugged in once inside the final sixteenth but took the lead with seventy yards to go. SPAN came off the rail with a half mile to go, was widest taking the bend, surged the last furlong, came up short but caught DENNIS'S PRIDE for second. DENNIS'S PRIDE emerged with the advantage after the first sixteenth of a mile, moved clear on the turn, lengthened command upper stretch, floated out slightly and began to wear down inside the final eighth. ITS MAMBO was hustled along to press DENNIS'S PRIDE from just outside, did not keep up on the bend, moved clear for second upper stretch but also did not have enough left the last furlong. KRUELESS prominent just outside ITS MAMBO, gave way after a half mile. BRUCE ATTACK reluctant to load, was away slowly once the race began, forwardly placed from outside on the backstretch, angled in on the bend and had little to offer for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Its Mambo
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled between, 2 wide turn, weakened last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Krueless
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed between, 3 wide turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Grayhop
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled out 1/4, 4 wide stretch bid, lugged in 1/16, got up late

ENTRY.NAME: Bruce Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: reluctant to load, away slowly, angled in turn, empty stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TORTUGA ISLAND stalked the early speed, went for the lead four wide on the bend, angled in some nearing the end of a half mile, took the advantage, moved clear under mild urging upper stretch then continued to draw off while ridden out the last furlong. TOO MUCH TUESDAY pressed from between rivals, was three wide into the turn, angled in behind TORTUGA ISLAND approaching the quarter pole, took over second inside the final eighth, moved clear inside the last sixteenth and lasted for the place. BABAS GAL hesitated then broke awkwardly, progressed from outside, was three wide leaving the bend, lodged a mild bid deep stretch and gained third. MOONSHINE MOLLY bumped with CASHMERE JUSTICE at the break, vied for the lead from inside, edged ahead into the turn, was soon challenged by TORTUGA ISLAND, no match for that one when set down for the drive and began to wear down inside the last furlong. RARE BEAUTY displayed early speed between horses but gave way with three furlong to go. CASHMERE JUSTICE bumped with MOONSHINE MOLLY at the start, was a contender from inside for nearly two and a half furlongs then steadily faded. DUE TO AN UNSAFE RAIL CONDITION, RACES FOUR THROUGH EIGHT WERE CANCELLED. ALL WAGERS EXCEPT A CONSOLATION DAILY DOUBLE FOR RACES THREE AND FOUR, AS WELL AS A CONSOLATION PICK 3 FOR RACES TWO, THREE AND FOUR, WERE REFUNDED.

ENTRY.NAME: Moonshine Molly
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, inside speed, no match for winner, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Too Much Tuesday
ENTRY.OWNER: Offspring Farm and Gavilsky II Lawrence J

ENTRY.NAME: Tortuga Island
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside bid turn, much the best, ridden out
